HEADWORD: Chronophotograph
<hw>Chron`o*pho"to*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
time + <ets>photograph</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of a set of photographs of
a moving object, taken for the purpose of recording and exhibiting
successive phases of the motion.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Chron`o*pho*tog"ra*phy</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
